    <h1>The Science of the Void</h1>
    <p class="lead">Vibrancy isn't a feeling; itâ€™s a measurable output. We use four primary metrics to determine if a zip code is thriving or merely insulating itself from reality.</p>
    
    <div class="metric-grid">
        <div class="metric-card">
            <h3>1. Acoustic Permeability</h3>
            <p>We calculate the "Sub-to-Shush" ratio. This measures how many decibels of bass a wall can handle before a neighbor mentions "work in the morning."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <h3>2. The Spice Constant</h3>
            <p>A density scan of local grocery stores. Points are deducted for neighborhoods where the "International" aisle is just three jars of mild salsa.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <h3>3. Beige Saturation Index</h3>
            <p>Using high-resolution satellite imagery, we detect levels of architectural boredom. A 90% concentration of Tan, Eggshell, or Sandstone paint triggers a "Void Alert."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
            <h3>4. The Friction Factor</h3>
            <p>Real-time analysis of HOA message boards. High frequencies of the phrases "excessive noise," "unapproved plants," or "curfew" signal a Critical Void event.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="formula-box">
        <h4>The Core Algorithm</h4>
        <code>Vibe = (Spice / Silence) * (Bass / Beige)</code>
        <p style="font-size: 11px; margin-top: 15px; color: #888;">*Final score is weighted against local street-mural density.</p>
    </div>
